  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if two-weeks of dosing with thiamphenicol is safe
      and is able to change the levels of certain pre-specified biomarkers in nervous tissue taken
      from the nasal passages.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Thiamphenicol has been proposed to increase the levels of the excitatory amino acid
      transporter 2 (EAAT2) in the nervous tissue. This study evaluated the ability of two weeks of
      treatment with thiamphenicol to increase EAAT2 in a nasal biopsy as a surrogate of brain
      nervous tissue.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
